Run 'make_installer.sh' first to download required packages.
This process requires Internet connection. The computer
running 'make_installer.sh' must have the same architecture
as computers in the cluster.

After download process finished, copy this folder to other
computers, and run 'install.sh'.

You could run script 'scripts/all_nodes.rb install' to do
automatical installation. Make sure you have modified
'scripts/nodelist.rb' according to cluster layout.
